body.text:
If you get bitten like this:
- Place the rat into a carrier (or similar) and temporarily separate it from humans and other rats;
- Rinse the wound under running warm water;
- Apply an antibacterial ointment;
- If the wound is deep or bleeding is significant, seek urgent/clinic care (cleaning/debridement and other care may be needed);
- For minor wounds, a bandage is usually enough to keep it clean, then let it air out after a few days;
- Bites near joints are more likely to cause follow-up problems; if swelling develops, have a clinician evaluate it.
